import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', bins=30)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts().reset_index().rename(columns={'index': 'origin', 'origin': 'count'})
    destination_counts = data['destination'].value_counts().reset_index().rename(columns={'index': 'destination', 'destination': 'count'})
    
    sns.barplot(x='origin', y='count', data=origin_counts, label='Origin', color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    sns.barplot(x='destination', y='count', data=destination_counts, label='Destination', color='red', alpha=0.5)
    
    plt.xlabel('Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the most common origin and destination for flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['date_count'] = data.groupby('date')['date'].transform('count')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='date_count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
